Taiwan Stocks Movers: Compal Electronics, HTC, Motech, Neo Solar

-- B y   W e i y i   L i m
-- 
2011-04-12T06:48:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/chunghwa-telecom-compal-electronics-taiwan-stocks-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
had unusual moves in Taiwan trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 1:30 p.m.  The Taiex Index fell 147.68, or 1.7 percent, to 8,732.59.  Solar-energy related stocks:  Neo Solar Power Corp. (3576)  (3576
TT) tumbled 7 percent to NT$68.30, the steepest loss since Sept.
27.  Sino-American Silicon Products Inc. (5483)  (5483 TT) slumped 6.9
percent to NT$121.50, its biggest loss since Oct. 4.  Motech
Industries Inc. (6244)  (6244 TT) lost 5.1 percent to NT$121, the
sharpest decline since Nov. 3.  The Economic Daily News cited Quincy Lin, chairman of Neo
Solar, as saying cell prices may fall in April on concern  Europe 
will cut back on solar subsidies in the second quarter. Thomas
Hsu, spokesman for Neo Solar, wasn’t immediately available for
comment at his office.  Compal Electronics Inc. (2324)  (2324 TT) declined 0.8 percent to
NT$29.70, the biggest retreat since April 1. First-quarter
revenue dropped to NT$164 billion ($5.6 billion) from NT$220
billion a year earlier, the Taipei-based maker of  laptop
computers  said in a statement yesterday. The average of four
analysts’ estimates compiled by Bloomberg was for revenue of
NT$198 billion.  HTC Corp. (2498)  (2498 TT) fell 4.2 percent to NT$1,150, tumbling
by the most since March 15. The shares have gained 33 percent
this year as of yesterday’s close. The stock trades at 15.1
times estimated earnings, more than the Taiex index’s multiple
of 13.1 times.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Weiyi Lim in Singapore at 
 wlim26@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
